  "worklog": "# brainTrade Work Log\n*Check this anytime to see what I'm doing and how I'm thinking.*\n\n## 2026-05-03 01:30 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 1] BTC downgraded to neutral after a large short reopened\n\n**Task:** Re-scan HL top-trader copy intelligence after BTC count weakened but net long held, and test whether the downgrade criteria finally triggered.\n\n**Finding:**\n- Both bots are alive (`pm-bot`, `hl-bot`).\n- Rotation pointed to **P1**.\n- Fresh tracker output: **BTC 6L/2S**, **ETH 4L/4S**, **SOL 3L/5S**.\n- Current top-book notional:\n  - **BTC:** longs **$13.88M** vs shorts **$4.74M** \u2192 net **+$9.14M long**\n  - **ETH:** longs **$0.09M** vs shorts **$34.72M** \u2192 net **-$34.63M short**\n  - **SOL:** longs **$0.22M** vs shorts **$11.04M** \u2192 net **-$10.82M short**\n  - **HYPE:** longs **$1.61M** vs shorts **$11.81M** \u2192 net **-$10.20M short**\n- BTC count improved from **4L/3S -> 6L/2S**, but that headline is misleading because a large short reopened.\n- New BTC short concentration: `anon-0x8fcc` **BTC SHORT $4.74M** plus `anon-0xff4c` tiny **BTC SHORT $67**.\n- BTC anchors rebuilt strongly: `anon-0xfc66` unchanged at **BTC LONG $5.63M**, `anon-0xecb6` rebuilt **$4.14M -> $5.24M**, and `anon-0x57dd` rebuilt **$2.34M -> $2.54M**.\n- Despite the long rebuild, the large `anon-0x8fcc` short dragged net BTC long below the key threshold: previous **+$11.89M**, current **+$9.14M**.\n- ETH remains the strongest bearish expression: net **-$34.63M**.\n- SOL remains bearish by count and notional: **3L/5S**, net **-$10.82M**.\n- HYPE remains secondary bearish: net **-$10.20M**.\n- I wrote the artifact to `/home/ubuntu/clawd/research/p1-btc-large-short-reopens-net-under-10m-2026-05-03-0130.md`.\n\n**My thinking:** The BTC downgrade trigger fired. Count looks healthier, but notional quality worsened because a single large BTC short reopened and net long dropped below `$10M`. Combined with P4 sentiment impulse-up + persistent expansion + BTC slipping, this is now crowded-fade risk, not a long-chase setup.\n\n**Decision:** Downgrade **BTC** from **bullish but mixed** to **neutral / crowded-fade risk**. Do not chase BTC longs. Keep **ETH short = strongest bearish expression**, **SOL short = bearish confirmed**, and **HYPE short = secondary bearish**. No HL trade opened; HL remains `notional_blocked`.\n\n**Next:** Watch `anon-0x8fcc` specifically. If the `$4.74M` BTC short closes and anchors stay long, BTC can recover to bullish-mixed. If the short grows or `anon-0xfc66`/`anon-0xecb6` trim, BTC becomes outright bearish/crowded-fade.\n\n## 2026-05-03 01:17 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 4] Expansion intensified while BTC slipped under hot sentiment\n\n**Task:** Refresh P4 alpha after the persistent low-risk / expanding / sentiment-crowding state and determine whether it cooled or intensified.\n\n**Finding:**\n- Both bots are alive (`pm-bot`, `hl-bot`).\n- Rotation pointed to **P4**.\n- Fresh alpha snapshot is `2026-05-03T01:17:03.018505+00:00`.\n- Classifier stayed **`mixed_transition`**.\n- PM risk stayed **low**.\n- Fast regime stay",
